name: I only Ever - screenprint
description:
I was going to name this something deep and profound, but a friend came up with "I ONLY EVER WANTED TO MARRY THE GIRL NEXT DOOR". 
Parfait.
Melancholy

Pink and yellow fluro with blue (not fluro because that is overload) and a heavy load of textured black over the top.
19" x 24" aprox
edition of 50

Each screenprint is handpulled and will differ in small ways to one another. 
Where the black lays over the underlying colours, it creates a slight ridge so from certain angles the full sweep of ink below can be seen.
They are not 'flat' screenprints, they're textured.

name: Housecleaning - screenprint
description:
Handpulled silkscreen print, edition of 50 in 3 different colour ways, fluro pink, fluro yellow or blue (not fluro!) plus black overlay.

The colour sweep pushes out passed the overlay... because thats what housecleaning feels like. 
Relentless.


Print size 40cm x 56cm or
15.75 inches x 22 inches aprox

PS
If you're Sydney, Australia based, Sweets Workshop, Summer Hill - 
http://www.sweetsworkshop.com/
has an exclusive run of these onto silver foil board (edition of 20), pick up only as they cannot be rolled.
